tly?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering constructor necessity for generated class**\\n\\nI’m wondering if a generated class might be invalid without a constructor. Although it might not matter too much, it seems \\\"behavioral\\\" classes should probably include a constructor. I could consider adding one using CodeEmitter with the right signature. But then, I start pondering whether a valid class really can exist without constructors — should they have at least one? Even if the verifier might fail without loading, I think I could use TransformingClassGenerator to ensure that the real class is accurate, including the constructor and delegate methods.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring ClassReader usage**\\n\\nI’m considering whether using ClassReader can avoid manual begin_class calls. It seems to call all methods when used properly. I think I could initialize it like this: ClassReader reader = new ClassReader(PlainService.class.getName()). I wonder if it loads the resource by name or from an InputStream in older versions of ASM. It seems I need to ensure it’s closed afterward. Using the class loader might be the way to go for loading resources if needed.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_6RAX3GCHinJQrbqdcbrSvwQb|fc_02e8be3f49ed44c9016a030cd848ac81969233be56f7f03141", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.sonatype.sisu.inject/cglib/2.2.1-v20090111/src/test/java/org_sonatype_sisu_inject/cglib/AddDelegateTransformerTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\n\nimport net.sf.cglib.core.Constants;\nimport net.sf.cglib.transform.impl.AddDelegateTransformer;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.objectweb.asm.ClassWriter;\nimport org.objectweb.asm.Type;\n", "newText": "import java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\n\nimport net.sf.cglib.transform.ClassReaderGenerator;\nimport net.sf.cglib.transform.TransformingClassGenerator;\nimport net.sf.cglib.transform.impl.AddDelegateTransformer;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.objectweb.asm.ClassReader;\nimport org.objectweb.asm.ClassWriter;\n"}, {"oldText": "    void emitsDelegateFieldAndForwardingMethodsForAbstractInterfaceMethods() {\n        final AddDelegateTransformer transformer = new AddDelegateTransformer(\n                new Class[] {GreetingContract.class},\n                GreetingDelegate.class\n        );\n        final ClassWriter writer = new ClassWriter(ClassWriter.COMPUTE_MAXS);\n        transformer.setTarget(writer);\n\n        transformer.begin_class(\n                Constants.V1_5,\n                Constants.ACC_PUBLIC,\n                \"org_sonatype_sisu_inject.cglib.GeneratedDelegatingService\",\n                Type.getType(PlainService.class),\n                Constants.TYPES_EMPTY,\n                \"GeneratedDelegatingService.java\"\n        );\n        transformer.end_class();\n\n        final byte[] generatedClass = writer.toByteArray();\n", "newText": "    void emitsDelegateFieldAndForwardingMethodsForAbstractInterfaceMethods() throws Exception {\n        final AddDelegateTransformer transformer = new AddDelegateTransformer(\n                new Class[] {GreetingContract.class},\n                GreetingDelegate.class\n        );\n        final ClassReader reader = readClass(PlainService.class);\n        final ClassWriter writer = new ClassWriter(ClassWriter.COMPUTE_MAXS);\n        final TransformingClassGenerator generator = new TransformingClassGenerator(\n                new ClassReaderGenerator(reader, 0),\n                transformer\n        );\n\n        generator.generateClass(writer);\n\n        final byte[] generatedClass = writer.toByteArray();\n"}, {"oldText": "    public interface GreetingContract {\n", "newText": "    private static ClassReader readClass(Class<?> type) throws Exception {\n        final String resourceName = type.getName().replace('.', '/') + \".class\";\n        try (InputStream input = ty